job description
data analytics scientist
position overview description
ford motor company's global data insight analytics gdia organization is looking for an analytics scientist that ha a deep understanding of data analysis and modeling you will have the opportunity to work with some of the brightest global subject matter expert that are transforming the automobile industry a a member of the advanced operational analytics team in this role you will lead initiative to leverage unique data stream using predictive analytics and machine learning to quantify the customer value of vehicle technology you will also support the development of optimization model that provide decision support to other ford organization such a product development strategy and sustainability
responsibilities
you will be responsible for providing the data analytics support for departmental task including assembly of data for building model and performing predictive prescriptive analytics more specifically you will
ingest large data set from a variety of source hadoop sql teradata oracle and 3rd party source in the public domain
identify key data element to extract decode analyze
lead the development of predictive analytics and machine learning algorithm using business critical datasets
use data analytics to gain insight into customer usage pattern and environmental condition to quantifying expected customer benefit such a fuel economy improvement cost reduction durability improvement and additional non-vehicle benefit
work collaboratively with various business group and region to disseminate critical information and develop strategic opportunity
job requirements
basic qualifications
master's degree in computer science mathematics statistics engineering management information systems business or related technical field
2+ year of academic or business experience in the following
a data analytics role including running query compiling data and manipulating data from separate source to form unified set for analysis
predictive analytics including machine learning and experience writing algorithm in python scala or other technical language
big data technology in the hadoop ecosystem hdfs mapreduce hive spark hue zeppelin etc and command line experience with loading and manipulating file within hdfs
preferred qualifications
phd in computer science mathematics statistics engineering management information systems or related technical field
knowledge of data transfer and ingestion technology including talend and hvr
demonstrated experience building visualization using tableau qlikview alteryx
strong oral written and interpersonal communication skill
proficiency in word excel and powerpoint
ability to write complex nosql query needed to identify analyze data
experience with spss ampl weka matlab r sas or similar software
experience working with global team
comfortable working in an environment where problem are not always well-defined and interested in learning new tool and technique
